cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 140 miles WSW of the Dry Tortugas
cyclone.trajectory: Expected to slow, meander over the southeastern Gulf, then turn north and finally northeast across the Florida peninsula toward the southeast U.S. coast.
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Big Bend near Cedar Key

weather_observation.watch_coast: Cuban provinces of La Habana, Artemisa, Mayabeque, Pinar del Rio, and the Isle of Youth
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Florida Keys, southern and central Florida peninsula, Florida Big Bend, and eventually northeast Florida and coastal Georgia/South Carolina
weather_observation.wind: Occasional tropical-storm-force gusts (mainly 25–35 kt) possible in squalls late Friday into Saturday.
weather_observation.storm_surge: Minor coastal run-up and elevated surf possible, but widespread surge >3 ft not expected.
weather_observation.rainfall: Bands could drop 2–4 inches of rain with localized higher totals, producing brief urban flooding.
weather_observation.other_hazards: High surf and dangerous rip currents along northeast Florida beaches late week.
